        if s == target:
            ans.append(list(t) + [])
            return
        if s > target:
            return
        for i in range(u, len(candidates)):
            c = candidates[i]
            t.append(c)
            dfs(s + c, i, t)
            t.pop()
    ans = []
    dfs(0, 0, [])
    return ans
